text: Nasibash () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Nasibashevsky Selsoviet, Salavatsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 951 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 15 km from Maloyaz. == References == Category:Rural localities in Salavatsky District
title: Nasibash
